COMPATIBLE OPEN-SOURCE PLATFORMS
1. COPERNICUS Programme
Integration Areas:
Copernicus Climate Change Service (C3S)
Copernicus Atmosphere Monitoring Service (CAMS)
Copernicus Marine Environment Monitoring Service
Satellite Earth observation data integration
Key Datasets:
ERA5 climate reanalysis data
Sentinel satellite imagery
Global atmospheric composition
Ocean and sea ice monitoring
2. NASA AWG (Atmospheric Working Group)
Integration Areas:
Earth Observing System Data and Information System (EOSDIS)
Global Modeling and Assimilation Office (GMAO)
Goddard Earth Sciences Data and Information Services Center
Key Datasets:
MERRA-2 (Modern-Era Retrospective analysis)
MODIS atmospheric products
CloudSat and CALIPSO data
Aura atmospheric composition
3. GEO BON (Group on Earth Observations Biodiversity Observation Network)
Integration Areas:
Essential Biodiversity Variables (EBVs)
Climate-biodiversity interaction studies
Ecosystem monitoring
Species distribution modeling under climate change
Key Focus:
Climate impact on biodiversity
Habitat change detection
Species migration patterns
Ecosystem resilience assessment
